problem_data.title: Increasing Triplet Subsequence
problem_data.description: Given an integer array nums, return true if there exists a triple of indices (i, j, k) such that i < j < k and nums[i] < nums[j] < nums[k]. If no such indices exists, return false.

examples.explanation: Any triplet where i < j < k is valid.
One of the valid triplet is (3, 4, 5), because nums[3] == 0 < nums[4] == 4 < nums[5] == 6.
